results.name: If k is a number with exactly two distinct decimal digits, say a and b, neither of which is 0 (i.e., a member of A101594), define the self-complement of k, SC(k), to be the number obtained by replacing a with b and vice versa. Then a(n) = lcm(A101594(n), SC(A101594(n))).
results.author: _Amarnath Murthy_, May 22 2003
ext: Corrected and extended by _David Wasserman_, Dec 07 2004
